race.comment: The well-related GILIANA (4) (half to G3 winner and G2 placed Garibaldi) has a win and a second from three outings over this course and distance and will be at peak fitness for this. Comes right into contention with the scratching of BUNDELLA and looks the one they all have to run down. KING SPIRIT (1) has placed five of six around this circuit and gets some weight relief from the inside alley. Ticks plenty of boxes and looms as the main danger. CARRIBEAN KING (3) saves his best form for this venue and is building up to another victory. May earn some minor money. KING OF THE JUNGLE (7) next in line. Something for the Multiples: LEVAR (6)
